What this is:
  An in-app member of your organization clicked "Request admin
  access" from their dashboard.  Admin access lets a member add
  CameraNodes, generate MCP API keys, configure recording policies,
  and access the audit log — programmatic and write-capable
  privileges you may or may not want them to have.

How to act on it:
  Review the request, then either grant or deny in Clerk's
  organization settings:
    {{ dashboard_url }}/settings

  Clerk is the source of truth for roles — promoting in Clerk
  takes effect within ~60 seconds via JWT refresh.

If you don't recognize the requester:
  Audit your member list immediately at the link above.  An
  unexpected promotion request from someone you don't know is
  a signal worth investigating before acting.

